    <main class="main">
        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Privacy & Data Usage</h1>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment dark">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What data is sent to my servers?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">ContainEye does not send any of your commands to my servers. SSH and test commands are only sent to your own servers, and no logs or session data are transmitted elsewhere.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/ai-wants-to-execute.png" alt="AI command execution confirmation" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment light">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>How does the AI work?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">AI is used only to suggest and modify tests, but it does not execute them. AI cannot execute commands without your confirmation during test creation.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/ai-has-question.png" alt="AI test suggestions" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="app-segment dark">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>What data does ContainEye collect?</h2>
                <p class="app-description">ContainEye collects anonymous, GDPR-compliant statistics about feature usage. This data is fully anonymized, and no personal data, server credentials, or command history is ever collected.</p>
                <img src="/images/containeye-framed/test-details-last-run-expected-output-last-output-fetch-current-output-done-delete.png" alt="Local test data storage" class="showcase-img">
            </div>
        </section>
